brewery.brewery_description: Heads of Noosa Brewing Co. is an Australian independently owned craft brewery located in Noosa on the Sunshine Coast. With a passion for lagers and a focus on quality, we strive to produce truly enjoyable beers for everyone.

beer.beer_description:
First brewed as a keg only release, we knew pretty quickly from customer feedback that we had to put this one in bottles straight away.
Introducing Heads of Noosa’s next Limited Release; the Japanese Black Lager. It’s a culmination and balance of two worlds... Delicate & dark. The delicateness of our Japanese Styled Lager, brewed with rice for its crisp, clean finish, meeting the world of roasted malt flavours that make it deliciously dark in flavour, light on the palate and easily enjoyable

A smooth Pale German Lager that carries a slight malt sweetness, with a clean gold hue to the eye and a soft, dry finish on the palate. Subtle hops and restrained bitterness create a balanced, refreshing & any-time beer. Prost!

beer.beer_description: Australian barley and rice play a lead role in creating this popular signature lager by Heads of Noosa. Brewed, fermented and filtered with precision. This lager is clean, crisp and delicately divine... for exceptional times.

Our LAGER 3.5 is a refreshing mid-strength beer brewed with a blend of base and specialty malts, fermented cold for a clean and crisp mouthfeel. This lager is filtered, making it easy on the eye, and the palate! Full-flavoured, but with 3.5% ABV you can stay for one more...

beer.beer_description: Australian barley and rice play a lead role in creating this popular signature lager by Heads of Noosa. Brewed, fermented and filtered with precision. This lager is clean, crisp and delicately divine... for exceptional times.

Australian barley and rice play a lead role in creating this popular signature lager by Heads of Noosa. Brewed, fermented and filtered with precision. This lager is clean, crisp and delicately divine... for exceptional times.
The embodiment of balance, this American Style Amber Lager is brewed with a blend of six malts and is delicately hopped. Inspired by the sunsets of Noosa, designed for after dark.

Our LAGER 3.5 is a refreshing mid-strength beer brewed with a blend of base and specialty malts, fermented cold for a clean and crisp mouthfeel. This lager is filtered, making it easy on the eye, and the palate! Full-flavoured, but with 3.5% ABV you can stay for one more...

The Bock is a German Strong lager, traditionally boasting big bold flavours and full body. We’ve taken that as inspiration but made it a little more approachable and easy drinking while maintaining a full flavour. This beer contains a blend of 6 different malts and is lightly dry hopped. There are strong caramel notes that balance a definite roastiness. The perfect lager to enjoy during the cooler months.

First brewed as a keg only release, we knew pretty quickly from customer feedback that we had to put this one in bottles straight away.
Introducing Heads of Noosa’s next Limited Release; the Japanese Black Lager. It’s a culmination and balance of two worlds... Delicate & dark. The delicateness of our Japanese Styled Lager, brewed with rice for its crisp, clean finish, meeting the world of roasted malt flavours that make it deliciously dark in flavour, light on the palate and easily enjoyable

Our take on a German style Pilsner. Easy drinking carrying a slight sweetness with a pleasant bitterness to balance, giving the beer a dry and refreshing finish. This Pilsner is a step from your standard Pilsner and is enjoyable year-round.

Big, bold and fermented cold like a true lager... meet the Baltic Porter! A delicious marriage of chocolate, caramel and raisin notes. At 7.8% this is one winter warmer you don’t want to miss. LIMITED RELEASE.
The India Pale Lager is a modern style with a hop forward character and a bigger body than most lagers. Our take on the style delivers the extra hop hit while still maintaining drinkability.

We’ve taken your favourite Japanese Lager to another level, introducing the Imperial Japanese Lager. Weighing in at 7.2%, with the same clean fermentation profile you’ve come to expect from the Japanese Lager, this beer has exceptional body and a bolder character as you’d expect from an Imperial.

Premium malts deliver this Doppelbock style beer beautiful chocolate/caramel-toffee characters. Hopped with German nobles to balance the delicate malt sweetness, this one is best enjoyed with friends...

A clean and crisp Bavarian style dark lager featuring Munich malts, providing complex flavours of toasted bread, caramel and hints of chocolate. Rounded by subtle fruity and spicy notes of the Noble hops whilst keeping the bitterness low. Traditionally crafted, full of flavour and too easily enjoyed.

A smooth Pale German Lager that carries a slight malt sweetness, with a clean gold hue to the eye and a soft, dry finish on the palate. Subtle hops and restrained bitterness create a balanced, refreshing & any-time beer. Prost!

Our Alcoholic Ginger Beer is infused with local Buderim Ginger providing a lovely kick of natural ginger spice, perfectly balanced with sweetness and subtle notes of lemon and lime, this is your ultimate refresher enjoyed anytime
